Natalia Perez was born and raised in North Hollywood, California to Mexican/Puerto Rican/Irish parents. Growing up in her household, music and culture served as the center of her upbringing. Natalia fell in love with the idea of broadcasting and radio when she was 8 years old.

Natalia started her radio career when she was 19-years-old, working for Clear Channel’s Top-40 station KIIS. In September 2009, she got her first on-air opportunity with MCM Entertainment co-hosting a nationally syndicated Top 40 Countdown show called “The Hot Hits Live from LA” that aired in 60 markets across Australia. 

In 2011 she began working with Hot 92.3 Los Angeles doing the Hollywood Reports with Rick Dees’ Morning show! In 2012 she continued working with Hot 92.3 on their new morning show hosted by Jimmy Reyes.

In April of 2014 Natalia began working with the Los Angeles Dodgers as a pre-game in stadium host and she continues to work with the Dodgers organization today.

In 2015 Big Boy brought his morning show to the newly flipped Real 92.3. With one team member short, Natalia was the only suggestion made by top execs to fill the void and from day one it was apparent why. She joined Louie G and Dj VickOne as a key members of Big Boy’s Morning Show. Today she can also be heard on Big Boy’s syndicated show, which airs in over 24 plus markets.
Natalia has a distinct voice and infectious personality. 

She loves music, movies and coffee. She also enjoys spending time with her one year old Son and Husband of 4 years and volunteering with her local YMCA. She’s extremely thankful to do what she loves and feels blessed to walk into the studio every day and have fun!

There are so many Hip Hop songs that are attached to core memories that make up my life so far! “Renegade” was the first Hip Hop song I fell in love with. “California Love” made me proud to be from the West Coast - “The Light” made realize Hip Hop was Love! “My Name Is” made me want to learn every lyric. Honestly, too many too name, you get the point. Hip Hop wasn’t suppose to last - but look at it now! The stories of Hip Hop need to be told and the music always makes us feel a certain way! I’m so lucky to have met some of the biggest icons in Hip Hop because of Big Boy and Real 92.3 🙏🏼I’m grateful everyday! Happy Birthday Hip Hop!
